race.comment: ROMANTIC LOVE (1) led for the judge last start over 1200m at Gilgandra but couldn't maintain the pressure and was swamped late in the piece. Yet to race beyond six furlongs in 12 career runs. Probably takes a sit just off the speed and will be tough to hold out. HANNAH'S BRIDGE (4) has been kept fresh since a comfortable win in a Class 1 over 1280m at Muswellbrook 45 days ago. Easily won a recent trial at Orange. Building a fine record and is good enough to stretch this field. The lightly raced TOM VEGAS (3) is back from a three-month spell. Last appeared when down the track in the Group 3 Gloaming Stakes. Best form will come over more ground but he is capable of sprinting well while fresh. SILENT ACE (2) returns from a 15-week spell for a second campaign. Scored an easy win here at this trip at his second career run back in August. Can run a big race. The consistent YIASOU (12) will make his own luck up front and might prove tough to catch.
